<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/rbline.gif">  
<H2>The ACLU continues to fight in state<BR> and federal courts across the
country.</H2>
<H4>This section of recent litigation will be expanded<BR> and reorganized in
coming weeks.</H4>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/rbline.gif">   
</CENTER>
<H3>Recent Cases</H3>
<DL>
<DT><BR> 
<B><A NAME="reno">American Civil Liberties Union et al. v. Janet Reno</A>  
</B> 
</DT>
<DD>Free speech in cyberspace is at stake as the first major legal challenge to
censorship on the Internet gets underway.  The case began when the ACLU filed a
motion for a temporary restraining order against indecency provisions of the
Telecommunications Bill immediately after it was signed into law by     
President Clinton on February 8.  The suit challenges provisions of the law that
criminalize making available to minors &quot;indecent&quot; or &quot;patently
offensive&quot; speech.  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/cdacom2.html">ACLU brief</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/cdacom.html">ACLU Complaint</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/issues/cyber/trial.htm">Updates and Documents</A>
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>    
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">     
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="Felker">Felker v. Turpin</A>
</B> 
</DT>
<DD>The question raised in this death penalty case from Georgia, is under what 
circumstances a state prisoner can file a second or successive habeas corpus
petition. Under the new terrorism act, a second or successive petition cannot be
filed unless the prisoner first receives permission from a three-judge panel of
the Court of Appeals, which, in turn, cannot grant permission unless the
petition fits within one of the very few exceptions to the general rule
established by Congress that second or successive petitions are not allowed. 

</DD>
<DD><BR>The Supreme Court directed the parties in the case to address three

questions:  1. Whether Congress can restrict the Supreme Court's appellate
jurisdiction in this way. 2. Whether the Supreme Court can exercise &quot;original&quot;
jurisdiction in a habeas action even if it cannot exercise appellate
jurisdiction. 3. Whether the new statute represents an unconstitutional &quot;suspension&quot;
of the writ of habeas corpus if the Supreme Court is left with no jurisdiction
at all. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/felker.html">Felker v. Turpin  Brief</A>

</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>    
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">     
<BR><BR>  
<B><A NAME="">Williams v. City of Pittsburgh</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> This action is brought by the named plaintiffs, individually and on behalf
of all other persons            similarly situated, seeking to end the defendant
City of Pittsburgh's historical and            long-standing practice of
condoning and acquiescing in unconstitutional conduct on the part            of
its police officers that has become accepted practice within the City's police
department.   
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/police.html">ACLU Complaint</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>    
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">     
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="Sheff">Sheff v O'Neill</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> In a 4-3 decision affirming the right of Hartford students to equal access
to education, the Conn. Supreme Court said that town boundaries are the single
largest cause of segregation in the state.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/sheffbrf.html">Sheff Brief (135k)</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>    
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">     
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="alegria">Armen Alegria et al.  v. Ronald J. D'Angelo,
Commissioner,   et. al.</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> Armen Alegria et. al. bring this civil-rights action to challenge conduct
of the defendants that has infringed  and continues to infringe the plaintiffs'
constitutional  rights of free association and free speech.  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/alegria.html">ACLU Complaint</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>    
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="sencion">Rafael Sencion  v. Rudolph Giuliani, Mayor of the City of
   New York et al.</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> Rafael Sencion brings this civil-rights action  to challenge the conduct
of defendant officials of the City of  New York that has infringed and continues
to infringe his free speech rights.  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/sencion.html">ACLU Complaint</A>  
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>      
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="jackson">Wisconsin v. Warner Jackson, et al.</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> At issue in this case, is the use of public funds to support religious
education.  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/jackson.html">ACLU brief</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">    
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="denver">Dr. Cecil Mciver, M.D.; C.B. (&quot;Chuck&quot;)
Castonguay; Robert G. Cron; And Charles E. Hall,  plaintiffs,   v.   Barry
Krischer, in his official capacity as State Attorney of the 15th Judicial
Circuit, et al.             </A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> Action challenges the ban on doctor-assisted suicide in Florida. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/mciver.html">ACLU complaint</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">    
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="denver">Denver Area Educational Telecommunications Consortium,
Inc. and American Civil Liberties Union  v.  Federal Communications Commission
and United States of America, et al.             </A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> This case questions sections 10(a) and 10(b) of the 1992 Cable Act, which
established a comprehensive scheme for censorship of &quot;indecent&quot;
programming on leased access channels. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/court/denver.html">ACLU brief</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.aclu.org/news/n021596b.html">Press Release</A>  
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="scott">Scott Family  vs.  John E. Samson, County Attorney for 
Washington County, et al.</A> 
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> The Scott Family was assaulted by the daughter's boyfriend and multiple
others after she indicated her intentions to have an abortion.  Also, several
public officials interfered in the plantiff's right to reproductive choice.  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/scott.html">ACLU Complaint</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="ahmad">Claims of Abraham Ahmad and Family Under the Federal Tort
Claims Act </A>     
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> Ahmad with support from the ACLU is seeking compensation for by several
government agencies following the Oklahoma bombing.  Ahmad was taken into
custody as a suspect in the bombing. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/ahmad.html">Claim on behalf of the Ahmad Family</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="vmi">United States of America, Petitioner,   v.   Commonwealth of
Virginia, et al. </A>     
</B> 
</DT>
<DD> This case concerns the exclussion of women from VMI since its founding in
1839.  &quot;Virginia's separate but unequal  education program for women falls
far short of satisfying the test of  intermediate scrutiny.&quot; 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/vmi.html">Summary of Argument in ACLU <I>amicus</I> brief</A>

</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT>  
<IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">   
<BR><BR> 
<B><A NAME="romer">Roy Romer,   As Governor of the State   of Colorado, and
the State   of Colorado, - v. - Richard G. Evans,et al.,
</A></B><BR></DT>
<DD>Does &quot;Amendment 2,&quot; a popularly enacted state constitutional

amendment that bars state and local government from enacting any laws or
policies that prohibit, or otherwise attempt to end, discrimination against gay
men, lesbians, and bisexuals, violate the Equal Protection Clause?
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/evans.html">Summary of Argument in ACLU Brief for
Respondent</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/aba.html">Summary of Argument in ABA <I>amicus</I> brief</A>

</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/evansdec.html">US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/evanssyl.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI></UL>
</DD></DL>
