<B><A NAME="mumia"> Mumia Abu-Jamal v. Price, et al</A> 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> &quot;Mr. Abu-Jamal's Motion For Preliminary Injunction claims that he has
been and is being punished for publishing a book, Live From Death Row, that is
highly critical of the Pennsylvania Department of Corrections (&quot;DOC&quot;).
&quot; 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/mumia.html">ACLU <I>amicus</I> brief </A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="mumia"> Curtis et al. v. School Committee of Falmouth et al.</A> 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD>In the first decision of its kind in the nation, the Supreme Judicial Court
of Massachusetts upheld a voluntary condom distribution program in the public
schools.  The Court's decision, issued on July 17, affirmed the legality of the
Falmouth school system's program against a challenge from parents represented by
attorneys affiliated with the radical right. The Civil Liberties Union of
Massachusetts and the national ACLU's Reproductive Freedom Project filed a
friend-of-the-court  brief on behalf of 30 AIDS prevention and other
organizations in support of the school district.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/curtis.html">Judicial Court of Massachusetts Decision</A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="hays">United States  v.  Hays et al.</A> 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>

<DL>
<DD> Decided June 29, 1995.  &quot;Appellees claim in this litigation that
Louisiana's congressional redistricting plan (Act 1) is a racial gerrymander
that violates the Fourteenth Amendment's Equal Protection Clause.&quot;  
