<P> 
<B><A NAME="rosen">Rosenberger et al.</A>                                     
      v.                            Rector and Visitors                    of
University  of Virginia et al. 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Decided June 29, 1995.  The University withheld payments for the printing
of a student publication on the grounds that the publication is prohibited by
University guidelines.  &quot;Petitioners filed this suit under 42 U.S.C. 1983, 
     alleging, inter alia, that the refusal to authorize payment violated their
First Amendment right to       freedom of speech.&quot;  
