<P> 
<B><A NAME="hurley">Hurley v. Irish-American Gay, Lesbian &amp; Bisexual Group
of Boston, 63 U.S.L.W. </A>4625 (1995)</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Argued April 25, 1995 and decided June 19, 1995, this case centers around 
 the refusal of the South Boston Allied War Veterans Council to allow   GLIB to
march in the Boston's annual St. Patrick's Day parade.  
