SRC="/graphics/ra.gif" BORDER="0">Listen to the arguments</A>
</LI></UL> 

<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P><B><A NAME="edmond">City of Edmonds  v.  Washington State Building Code
Council, et. al.</A> 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Decided May 15, 1995, the issue of this case is whether the City of
Edmund's zoning ordinance is exempt from the    Fair Housing Act under 42 U.S.C.
section 3607(b)(1), which provides that nothing in the Act &quot;limits the 
applicability of any reasonable local, State or Federal restrictions regarding

the maximum number of  occupants permitted to occupy a dwelling.&quot;  
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/edmund2.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/edmund.html">Summary of Argument in ACLU <I>amicus</I>
brief</A> 
</LI></UL>
