<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="evans">Arizona v. Evans</A></B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Argued December 7, 1994-Decided March 1, 1995.   The exclusionary rule is
at the center of this case.  Evan's car was searched after the patrol car's
computer indicated that there was an outstanding misdemeanor warrant.  The
search revealed a bag of marijuana.  The misdemeanor had been resolved prior to
the search, so the respondent moved to have it suppressed. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/evan2.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/evan.html"> Summary of Argument in ACLU <I>amicus</I>
brief </A> 
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="swint">Swint et al.                                             v.
                Chambers County Commission et al.</A>  
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Argued January 10, 1995-Decided March 1, 1995.   Owners of a nightclub in
Chambers County Alabama  petititoned the court, seeking &quot;damages and other
relief under 42 U. S. C. 1983 for alleged civil rights violations.&quot; 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/swint2.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/swint.html">Summary of Argument in ACLU <I>amicus</I>
brief</A> 
</LI></UL> 
<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="green">Eloise Anderson,       CA Dept of Social Services, et al., 
                                           v.                       Deshawn
Green, Debby Venturella                            and Diana P. Bertollt, etc.</A>

</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> The question presented in this case is &quot;Whether a State's denial to
newer bona fide residents of <I>Aid to Families With Dependent Children</I>
(AFDC) benefits equal to those granted to longer-term residents is
unconstitutional.&quot; 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/green2.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/court/green.html">Summary of Argument in ACLU <I>amicus</I>
brief</A>  
</LI></UL>
<P></P></DD>
<DT></DT></DL><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif">
<P> 
<B><A NAME="treas">United States et al.                                       
    v.                   National Treasury Employees Union et al. </A> 
</B> 
</P>
<P></P>
<DL>
<DD> Decided February 22, 1995.  The National Treasury Employees Union is
questioning the constitutionality of  501(b) of the Ethics in Government Act of
1978, which prohibits government employees from accepting honorarium. 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/court/treas2.html">Syllabus of US Supreme Court Decision</A> 
</LI>
