<center>
<h1>Featured Civil Liberties Sites</h1></center>
<blockquote>
<P>
With thousands of sites on the web pertaining to civil liberties issues, it's 
sometimes hard to keep up with the truly outstanding ones.  To help make sure you 
stay up on what's out there, every week the ACLU will spotlight a civil liberties-related site.  
All you have to do is click and go.  
</blockquote>
<P>
<img src="http://www.aclu.org/graphics/redline.gif" width="100%">
<P>
<h3>This week's site:</h3>
<DL>
<DD><a href="http://www-leland.stanford.edu/group/King/mlkpp.htm">
<b>The Martin Luther King, Jr. Papers Project at Stanford University</a></b>
<P>
This site contains a chronology of Dr. King's life, an unedited biography, and information about the Papers Project.  In addition, there is a fully searchable bibliography, with over 2700 references "to works that deal with the life and work of Martin Luther King, Jr., and the civil rights movement."  The site is under construction.
<P>


</DL>
