<img src="/graphics/abouthdr.gif"><h2>Loren Siegel - Director of Public Education for the ACLU</h2>
<img src="/graphics/lsiegel.jpg"><P>
Loren Siegel is the Director of Public Education for the American Civil
Liberties Union. As public education director, she is responsible for the
coordination of the ACLU's communications-related programs, including media
relations, publications and special projects that promote public
understanding of civil liberties and the Bill of Rights.
<P>
Prior to joining the ACLU, Siegel was a partner in the law firm of Gladstein,
Reif & Siegel, where she specialized in labor law, government benefits and
domestic relations. She has also worked with the New York Civil Liberties
Union and has served as an adjunct assistant professor at Queens College,
Urban Studies Department.
<P>
Siegel has written widely about various civil liberties issues, including the
rights of the mentally ill, and, more recently, about drug policy and law
enforcement issues. She has also spoken extensively around the country.
<P>
A graduate of Rutgers Law School and Bennington College, she is the mother of
two children and she resides in Brooklyn, New York.
<P>
