<H3><A NAME="3"></A>Criminal Justice</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><A NAME="7092"></A><IMG SRC="/graphics/as7092.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><I>All
God's Children: The Bosket Family and the American Tradition of Violence</I></B><BR><I>by
Fox Butterfield</I><BR>(Knopf, 1996, 389pp.) Cloth.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>This stunning book by a <I>New York Times</I> crime reporter traces the
seemingly inevitable destruction of top potentially valuable lives -- Willie
Bosket, deemed the &quot;most violent criminal in New York State history,&quot;
and his father -- each first incarcerated at age nine, each ultimately convicted
of murder.  A startling examination of an American legacy of violence, from the
pre-Revolutionary South to today's urban America.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><A HREF="/store/goodread.html#7092">More information about <I>All God's
Children</I></A></P>
<TABLE BORDER="0" ALIGN="CENTER">
<TR>
<TD><B>Item #7092</B></TD>
<TD WIDTH="40"><BR></TD>
<TD><A HREF="/cgi-bin/aclu/store/as.pl?AddItem=7092&session=970213072055_93&page=book1.html&lastpage=">Order Item</A></TD></TR>
