<H3><A NAME="8"></A>Racial Equality</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><A NAME="1126"></A><IMG SRC="/graphics/as1126.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" BORDER="0"><B><I>Antidiscrimination
Law and Social Equality</I></B><BR><I>by Andrew Koppelman</I><BR>(Yale
University Press, 1996, 276pp.)</P>
<P>The author argues the modern conception of antidiscrimination law, as a
project of cultural transformation, is consistent with -- and even demanded by
-- principles of liberty.</P>
<P><A HREF="/store/goodread.html#1126">More information about <I>Antidiscrimination
Law and Social Equality</I></A></P>
