of Freedom: Racial Politics and Presumptions of the American Legal Process</I></B><BR><I>by
A. Leon Higgenbotham, Jr.</I><BR>(Oxford University Press, 1996, 304
pp.,Cloth.)</P>
<P>A seminal work by a federal judge and major scholar in the field of race and
the legal system.</P>

