<TD><A HREF="/cgi-bin/aclu/store/as.pl?View=1&session=970213072055_93&page=book1.html&lastpage=">View Order</A></TD></TR></TABLE>
<HR>
<P><A NAME="1127"></A><IMG SRC="/graphics/as1127.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" BORDER="0"><B><I>Tragic
Failure: Racial Integration in America</I></B><BR><I>by Tom Wicker</I><BR>(William
Morrow, 1996, 218pp., Cloth)</P>
<P>The former <I>New York Times</I> political columnist analyzes the failure
of integration, and how race has become a subtext for all political debate, from
affirmative action to poverty, crime, unemployment and welfare.</P>
<P><A HREF="/store/goodread.html#1127">More information about <I>Tragic
Failure</I></A></P>
