<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Steven Shapiro </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/abouthdr.gif"><h2>Steven Shapiro - Legal Director of the ACLU</h2><P><img src="/graphics/shapiro.gif" align="left"><blockquote>
Steven R. Shapiro is the Legal Director of the American Civil Liberties
Union, the nation's oldest and largest civil liberties organization. As Legal
Director, he supervises a staff of nearly 50 lawyers that are involved in
hundreds of civil liberties cases throughout the country. Among other duties,
Shapiro directly supervises the extensive litigation activities of the ACLU
before the U.S. Supreme Court. The ACLU routinely participates in more
Supreme Court cases each year than any other private organization.
<P>
Shapiro is also an adjunct professor of constitutional law at Brooklyn Law
School, specializing in free speech issues.
<P>
After graduating from Harvard Law School and spending one year as law clerk
to Judge J. Edward Lumbard of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Second
Circuit, Shapiro joined the New York Civil Liberties Union in 1976.
Throughout his career, he has been involved in a wide variety of civil
liberties controversies. In 1987, he argued and won a case before the U.S.
Supreme Court limiting the power of the government to exclude foreign
speakers from the United States because of their political views. He is also
a frequent speaker on civil liberties questions.
<P>
Shapiro is a member of the Board of Directors of the Lawyers Committee for
Human Rights, and the Steering Committee of the Fund for Free Expression.
<P>
</blockquote>

