<HEAD>
<TITLE> ACLU News Wire -2/6/97 Maryland Motor Vehicles Department
 Sells Privacy Down the River </TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif">

<P><TT>February 6, 1997: Maryland Motor Vehicles Department
 Sells Privacy Down the River
</TT></P>

<P></P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/rbline.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<P><TT>BALTIMORE -- The practice of selling personal information by the Maryland Motor Vehicles Administration has raised lots of money as well as privacy concerns, the Washington Times reports.</TT></P>

<P><TT>Over the past two years, MVA has grossed $5.7 million dollars by selling people's driver's liscense records to independent companies. Baltimore's MVA sells records either in bulk, giving 10,000 records for $500, or individually at $5 a piece.</TT></P>

<P><TT>Bankers, retailers, private investigators and insurance companies have all been known to purchase thousands of records from MVA and use the lists for subscription programs through mail solicitation.</TT></P>

<P><TT>The amount of money that MVA raises is relatively small, and not a &quotcompelling&quot justification for violating people's privacy rights, said Susan Goering, the executive director of the American Civil Liberties Union in Maryland.</TT></P>

<P><TT>&quotIt's bad enought that private concerns are [selling records], but to have the government making use of our personal information is outrageous,&quot Goering said. &quotI think the role of government is to protect people from the invasions of privacy that already exist.&quot</TT></P>

<P><TT>Until now, the choice about the distribution of one's information has existed, but not been publicized in Maryland. Out of the 3 million people that have drivers' liscenses, only 6,018 have made that choice since 1985.</TT></P>

<P><TT>&quotIt's bad enough that privacy concerns are compromised by this practice, but the fact that people aren't informed about the option of sealing their records is even worse,&quot Goering said.
</TT></P>



</BLOCKQUOTE>




<P></P>
<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG
SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP="ISMAP" BORDER="0"></A></CENTER>
